licence_overview:
If you fish for salmon, eels or freshwater fish in Northern Ireland you must have a licence from the right agency.  These are:

* [Department of Culture, Arts and Leisure (DCAL)](http://www.dcalni.gov.uk/ "Department of Culture, Arts and Leisure"){:rel="external"} 
* [Loughs Agency of the Foyle,  Carlingford](http://www.loughs-agency.org/ "Loughs Agency"){:rel="external"} 
* [Irish Lights Commissions (FCILC).](http://www.dardni.gov.uk/index/contact-us/a-z-of-contributors/fisheries-division/fisheries-contacts/fcilc-contacts.htm "Irish Lights Commissions"){:rel="external"}

The agency you need to contact will depend on where you wish to fish.

You must also have a permit from the fishery owner.

You must comply with any terms and conditions attached to a licence and permit.

*[DCAL]: Department of Culture, Arts and Leisure 
*[FCILC]: Foyle, Carlingford and Irish Lights Commissions
